# Felicity Event Management System - Development Tasks Breakdown

**Date:** February 22, 2026
**Project:** Felicity Event Management System (MERN)
**Current Status:** Planning Phase - 0% Implementation

---

## Overview

The system will centralize event management for Felicity, handling participants, organizers, and admins. It uses the MERN stack with JWT authentication and role-based access control.

---

## Task 1: Foundation & Authentication Setup

### Goal
Setup backend/frontend boilerplate, database schema, and authentication systems.

### Estimated Duration
**1 Sprint**

### Sub-tasks
#### 1.1 Backend Initialization & Database
- [ ] Setup Express server and MongoDB connection
- [ ] Configure environment variables & error handling middlewares

#### 1.2 Models & Schemas
- [ ] Create Participant model (IIIT/Non-IIIT, preferences)
- [ ] Create Organizer model
- [ ] Create Admin model

#### 1.3 Auth Controllers & Routes
- [ ] Implement `POST /api/auth/register` (Participant)
- [ ] Implement `POST /api/auth/login` (Participant, Organizer, Admin)
- [ ] Set up JWT middleware and bcrypt hashing
- [ ] Implement script to seed Admin user

#### 1.4 Frontend Foundation
- [ ] Initialize React app (Vite/CRA) and configure Tailwind CSS
- [ ] Setup React Router
- [ ] Setup State Management (Context API / Zustand)
- [ ] Setup Axios instance with JWT request/response interceptors

#### 1.5 Auth UIs
- [ ] Build Login Screen (handling all roles)
- [ ] Build Participant Signup Screen (Email domain validation for IIIT)
- [ ] Implement Protected route wrappers for each role state

### Required API Endpoints
- `POST /api/auth/register`
- `POST /api/auth/login`

